&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Claims and Change Specialist&lt;/strong&gt; to support large, heavy-civil infrastructure programs, including highways, roads, bridges, transit (both rail and bus), international airports, and water/wastewater projects delivered through both traditional and alternative methods. Your primary focus will be supporting claims analysis, contract administration, and change management activities associated with complex infrastructure construction projects, including contract research, change control, commercial management support, and coordination with project controls and construction management teams.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a long-term, full-time, on-site position located in New York, NY.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;may include, but are not limited to, the following:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support the review of contractor notices, change requests, contract modifications, and related documentation through contract research and claims analysis.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in evaluating entitlement considerations by reviewing contract requirements, technical documentation, project records, and applicable procedures.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Draft correspondence related to contract changes, requests for clarification, and change management activities for management review.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare written summaries, analyses, and supporting documentation outlining contractual considerations, findings, and key project issues.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support administration of the change control process in accordance with contract requirements, project procedures, and established change management practices.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review and track change requests to help ensure compliance with contractual requirements, documentation standards, and established timelines.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Compile, maintain, and organize supporting documentation associated with change requests, including cost, schedule, technical, and project controls information.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain accurate records of change orders, approvals, correspondence, negotiations, and supporting documentation within project tracking systems and change logs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate with estimators, schedulers, project controls teams, construction management staff, contractors, and stakeholders to facilitate the collection and organization of information related to proposed changes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule and coordinate change management meetings, prepare meeting materials, and document action items, decisions, and follow-up activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in the preparation and review of change proposal requests and related documentation.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support change order negotiations by coordinating meetings, preparing materials, documenting discussions, and tracking outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist in ensuring change management activities comply with applicable contract requirements, procurement guidelines, project procedures, and audit requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Organize and maintain project records to support internal and external audits related to contract compliance and change management activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attributes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational and analytical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative mindset that fosters teamwork, trust, and positive relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Natural curiosity, problem-solving abilities, and a passion for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
