&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Project Scheduler&lt;/strong&gt; to support large, complex heavy-civil infrastructure programs, including highways, roads, bridges, transit (both rail and bus), international airports, and water/wastewater projects delivered through both traditional and alternative delivery methods. Your primary focus will be developing, maintaining, and analyzing integrated project schedules that support the successful delivery of a major rail systems modernization program.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a long-term, full-time, hybrid position located in San Francisco, CA. Team members are expected to work from the project office approximately three days per week.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;may include, but are not limited to, the following:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and update integrated project schedules using Oracle Primavera P6.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build and manage baseline schedules that accurately reflect engineering, procurement, construction, systems integration, testing, commissioning, and project milestones.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Analyze schedule performance, critical path activities, float consumption, schedule risks, and forecasted completion dates.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Coordinate schedule development and monthly updates with project managers, engineering teams, contractors, consultants, and client stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review contractor schedules for compliance with project requirements, schedule logic, sequencing, durations, and milestone commitments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate schedule impacts resulting from scope changes, delays, recovery plans, and time impact analyses.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare schedule reports, milestone updates, look-ahead schedules, and executive-level schedule presentations.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with project controls, cost management, risk management, and change management teams to support integrated program controls.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Participate in project meetings and provide schedule analysis and recommendations that support informed decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain scheduling standards, procedures, and best practices while ensuring schedule quality and consistency throughout the project lifecycle.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Attributes&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent written and verbal communication and interpersonal skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Excellent organizational and analytical skills.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborative mindset that fosters teamwork, trust, and positive relationships.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Natural curiosity, problem-solving abilities, and a passion for continuous improvement.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to manage multiple priorities and deadlines in a complex project environment.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong attention to detail and commitment to quality, accountability, and professionalism.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Minimum Qualifications&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in engineering, construction management, project management, or related field, or equivalent combination of education and experience.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;10+ years of experience developing and managing CPM schedules for large infrastructure, transportation, rail, transit, or heavy civil construction programs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expert-level proficiency with Oracle Primavera P6, including development and maintenance of complex CPM schedules, critical path analysis, schedule forecasting, and reporting.&lt;/li&gt;
