&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;About the Position&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a &lt;strong&gt;Senior Scheduler&lt;/strong&gt; who will work on large, complex heavy civil rail transit projects where you’ll utilize your expertise in Communications Based Train Controls (CBTC). The Senior Scheduler partners closely with project managers, design engineers, operations leaders, contractors, and stakeholders to validate scope, resources, and constraints against accurate, executable schedules. This role serves as the scheduling subject-matter expert and provides analytical insight to support decision-making, risk mitigation, and claims management.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This is a long term, full-time, on-site position located in New York, NY.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;em&gt;may include, but are not limited to, the following:&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop, maintain, and analyze integrated project schedules for multiple concurrent design and construction projects, ensuring alignment with project scope, contractual milestones, resource plans, and client objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Review, evaluate, and recommend approval of contractor-submitted baseline and updated CPM schedules, verifying schedule logic, durations, sequencing, milestones, constraints, and compliance with contractual and organizational requirements.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop baseline schedules and perform detailed schedule analyses, including critical path and near-critical path evaluation, float analysis, resource loading, cost loading, cost curves, resource histograms, and schedule comparisons.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Monitor project progress against approved baseline schedules by validating contractor-reported progress with field teams, forecasting completion dates, identifying schedule variances, and recommending corrective actions.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform schedule change management activities, including detailed review and analysis of change orders, schedule revisions, and contractor schedule updates to assess impacts on project delivery.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Conduct Time Impact Analyses (TIA), schedule delay analyses, and what-if scenario modeling to evaluate potential impacts, support claims management, and develop schedule recovery strategies.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform earned value management (EVM) analyses and support Quantitative Schedule Risk Assessments (QSRA) to evaluate project performance, schedule risk, and forecasted outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify schedule risks, critical path activities, potential delays, and emerging issues, providing recommendations to mitigate impacts and improve schedule performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and present weekly, monthly, and ad hoc schedule reports, executive briefings, dashboards, and management presentations that communicate project status, critical milestones, schedule trends, recovery plans, and key performance metrics.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain short-term look-ahead schedules to support construction sequencing, operational planning, and coordination among project stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Facilitate schedule review meetings and collaborate with project managers, design teams, contractors, procurement, operations, subject matter experts, and client stakeholders to resolve scheduling issues and maintain schedule alignment across all project activities.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report potential track outages and other schedule-sensitive operational constraints within the project management information system to support planning and decision-making.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure schedules comply with organizational standards, contractual requirements, scheduling best practices, and industry guidelines while maintaining schedule integrity through ongoing quality reviews an

